December
UBA changes pay-off line

The UBA Group has repositioned its brand essence and pay-off line to align with the group vision of becoming the ‘undisputed leader and dominant financial services institution in Africa’.

The new pay-off line, ‘Africa’s global bank’ became apparent after using extensive research and feedback from customers, staff and other stakeholders, and in line with our evolving business strategy – which is to become a Pan African bank with global footprint.

Designed to “bond with our essence” and truly define what the Bank stands for, the group’s new strategy replaces the successful ‘The Wise Choice’ payoff line that made banking services accessible to the lower masses. The new brand pay-off, “Africa’s global bank” traverses different sub-sectors within the financial services industry (e.g UBA Capital London), different customer segments and geographical borders. “Africa’s global bank” bespeaks of our position today and our aspirations for the future.

Our stakeholders have a reason to believe in this new pay-off line as UBA remains an African owned and managed financial solutions powerhouse. Over the years, UBA has attained some of the highest industry ratings and its talent pool (employee skills & experiences) rivals that of any other global financial services player.

Currently the UBA Group already has 12 world-class Divisions, each providing specialised/targeted financial services solutions to a broad market base. Our African play - UBA already has operations in Nigeria (Africa’s most populous country), Ghana (a key player in the west African sub-region), Cameroon, Ivory Coast and others soon to be disclosed across sub-Saharan Africa).

Our Western play - UBA is the only African bank with dual regulatory presence in both North America (New York) and the United Kingdom (London) - with more to come in the Middle East and Europe. UBA has also recently established a representative office in China.

31
October
Elizabeth Grabs Gh2,000 In 3WM Promotion[

Elizabeth Asamoah became the proud winner of Two Thousand Ghana Cedis when she was selected as the 3rd Wise Millionaire at the 3rd draw of the “3 Wise Millionaires” savings promotion held on October 31, 2007. She joins Patrick Tetteh and Lawrence Addae who were selected as the 1st and 2nd Wise Millionaire respectively.

Other 19 customers were also selected as winners of the 3rd draw with prizes ranging from stand-by generators, table top fridges, home theatre sets and branded gift items among others.

Delivering a speech at the function, the Divisional Head of Institutional Banking – Mr Daniel Addo, said that more persons in Ghana through UBA have now being empowered to own and operate their bank accounts as a result of the banks low minimum opening amount and operating balance.

He was of the conviction that the conservative lot in the public had reacted positively and taken advantage of the savings promotion which was launched in April.

He emphasized that UBA Ghana will continue to move quickly and confidently to provide customers with best-of-thought solutions and services, combined with best of breed technologies. He congratulated the winner and wished her well.


 

18
September
Minister Of Finance Launches UBA Moneygram

The strategic partnership between UBA Ghana and Moneygram International was out-doored at the center of Accra at Kwame Nkrumah circle on Tuesday September 18, 2007 by the Minister of Finance and Economic Planning, Honourable Kwadwo Baah-Wiredu.

In attendance was Mr Nnamdi Okonkwo - MD/CEO of UBA Ghana, Alhaji Amadu Montia - Assistant Director – Banking Supervision Department of the Bank of Ghana, Miss Spottiswoode – Africa Regional Director for Moneygram International as well as other representatives, other distinguished invited guests, our valued customers and members of the general public.’

In his welcome address, Mr Nnamdi Okonkwo mentioned UBA Ghana will create marketing initiatives for the tremendous growth of MoneyGram transactions in Ghana in a bid to bringing banking services closer to people. He revealed that the bank was currently making preparations to open 5 more additional branches by the end of the year and an additional 15 by the end of the next financial year ending 2008. He concluded his remarks by announcing that all UBA-Moneygram recipients will receive free mobile phone units to call the sender and say “thank you’ till the end of the year.

In his keynote address, the Minister of Finance and Economic planning commended UBA for introducing new and exciting products onto the Ghanaian market. He urged banks set their lending rates in line with the downward trend of inflation and the Central Bank’s prime rate. He called on UBA Ghana to play a significant role by promoting remittances and helping to channel funds to finance consumption and investment in many areas.

March
UBA Makes Banking Easier With Wise Alert

After consolidating its position as a market leader in product innovation, UBA Ghana moved a stepped ahead once again with the launch of the Wise Alert product on March 28, 2007 at the Ghana International Press Centre.

Briefing the media on this innovative product, Mr Nnamdi Okonkwo – MD/CEO of UBA Ghana said that the Wise Alert product will allow customers to receive instant SMS/ e-mail notifications when transactions occur on their account.

He noted that busy people with limited time to visit the bank could still monitor their account status while on the move. Again salaried workers will not need to visit the bank to enquire whether salaries have been paid or not, thus saving time and cost. Apart from this, customers would be able to detect fraudulent transactions in time.

Mr Okonkwo concluded his remarks when he reiterated that the introduction of the new product was a further demonstration of the bank’s commitment to more customer and value driven products.

28
February
Nnamdi Okonkwo Speaks On Chinese Presence

“We must not see their presence as a threat but rather look for opportunities to collaborate with them”. This was the advice of the MD/CEO of UBA Ghana, Mr Nnamdi Okonkwo, when he led a discussion on “The Growing Chinese penetration into Ghana and Africa” at the fourth Daily Express breakfast series.

The event was held at the Alisa Hotel on February 28, 2007 and participants at the event included the Government Spokesperson on Finance Mr Kwaku Kwarteng, officials from the CDD, representatives from GUTA, other FMCG companies and the media.

Mr Okonkwo further advised local businesses to take advantage of the presence of Chinese investors into the Ghanaian economy. He suggested that the business community should work together with parliament for a collaborative framework between the two countries.
